snippet.textDisplay:
This is just an attempt to help the non-Tamils to get the feel. A cultural experience must help to a great extent to understand the feel. 

The love song is set as a protective husband leaves to work at his paddy fields.

Husband: don’t  come to the courtyard
                   Don’t chew betel leaves until     the mouth turns red 
                   Don’t use black Bhindi my   darling 
                    Ppl might feel jealous; I am going to the fields  

Wife:  I’ll not come to the courtyard 
           I’ll not chew betel leaves until my mouth turns red 
            I’ll not have black bhindi, my dear
            No one would feel jealous, you go to the fields.
